Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: 26 days from today you and millions of Americans will choose two people to lead us into the future as president and vice president of the United States.
Speech: 26 days from today you and millions of Americans will choose two people to lead us into the future as president and vice president of the United States.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Our opponents say, things are okay.
Speech: Our opponents say, things are okay.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Don't rock the boat.
Speech: Don't rock the boat.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Not to worry.
Speech: Not to worry.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: They say we should be satisfied.
Speech: They say we should be satisfied.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: But I don't think we can be satisfied when we're spending $150 billion a year in interest alone on the national debt, much of it going to foreign bankers; or when 25 percent of our high school students are dropping out of school; or when we have 2-1/2 million of our fellow citizens, a third of them veterans, who are homeless and living on streets and in doorways in this country, when Mr. Bush's prescription for our economic future is another tax giveaway to the rich.
Speech: But I don't think we can be satisfied when we're spending $150 billion a year in interest alone on the national debt, much of it going to foreign bankers; or when 25 percent of our high school students are dropping out of school; or when we have 2-1/2 million of our fellow citizens, a third of them veterans, who are homeless and living on streets and in doorways in this country, when Mr. Bush's prescription for our economic future is another tax giveaway to the rich.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: We can do better than that.
Speech: We can do better than that.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Not working with government alone, but all of us working together.
Speech: Not working with government alone, but all of us working together.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Lloyd Bentsen and I are optimists, and so are the American people.
Speech: Lloyd Bentsen and I are optimists, and so are the American people.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: And we ask you for our hand for your hands and your hearts, and your votes on the 8th of November so we can move forward in the future.
Speech: And we ask you for our hand for your hands and your hearts, and your votes on the 8th of November so we can move forward in the future.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Kitty and I are very grateful to all of you for the warmth and the hospitality that you've given to us in your homes and communities all across this country.
Speech: Kitty and I are very grateful to all of you for the warmth and the hospitality that you've given to us in your homes and communities all across this country.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: We love you, and we're grateful to you for everything that you've given to us.
Speech: We love you, and we're grateful to you for everything that you've given to us.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: And we hope that we'll be serving you in the White House in January of 1989.
Speech: And we hope that we'll be serving you in the White House in January of 1989.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: Thank you, and God bless you.
Speech: Thank you, and God bless you.
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: (Applause)
Speech: (Applause)
Speaker: DUKAKIS
Name: Michael S. Dukakis

Text: BUSH: Sometimes it does seem that a campaign generates more heat than light.
Speech: Sometimes it does seem that a campaign generates more heat than light.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: So let me repeat, I do have respect for my opponent, for his family, for the justifiable pride he takes in his heritage.
Speech: So let me repeat, I do have respect for my opponent, for his family, for the justifiable pride he takes in his heritage.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But we have enormous differences.
Speech: But we have enormous differences.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to hold the line on taxes, and keep this the longest expansion in modern history going until everybody in America benefits.
Speech: I want to hold the line on taxes, and keep this the longest expansion in modern history going until everybody in America benefits.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to invest in our children.
Speech: I want to invest in our children.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Because I mean it when I say I want a kinder and gentler nation.
Speech: Because I mean it when I say I want a kinder and gentler nation.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And by that I want to have child care where the families, the parents, have control.
Speech: And by that I want to have child care where the families, the parents, have control.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to keep our neighborhoods much, much better in terms of anti-crime, and that's why I would appoint judges that have a little more sympathy for the victims of crime and a little less for the criminals.
Speech: I want to keep our neighborhoods much, much better in terms of anti-crime, and that's why I would appoint judges that have a little more sympathy for the victims of crime and a little less for the criminals.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: That's why I do feel if some police officer is gunned down that the death penalty is required.
Speech: That's why I do feel if some police officer is gunned down that the death penalty is required.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to help those with disabilities fit into the mainstream.
Speech: I want to help those with disabilities fit into the mainstream.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: There is much to be done.
Speech: There is much to be done.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: This election is about big things.
Speech: This election is about big things.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And perhaps the biggest is world peace.
Speech: And perhaps the biggest is world peace.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I ask you to consider the experience I have had in working with a President who has revolutionized the situation around the world.
Speech: And I ask you to consider the experience I have had in working with a President who has revolutionized the situation around the world.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: America stands tall again, and as a result, we are credible.
Speech: America stands tall again, and as a result, we are credible.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And we have now achieved an historic arms control agreement.
Speech: And we have now achieved an historic arms control agreement.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I want to build on that.
Speech: I want to build on that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I'd love to be able to say to my grandchildren, four years after my first term, I'd like to say, your grandfather, working with the leaders of the Soviet Union, working with the leaders of Europe, was able to ban chemical and biological weapons from the face of the earth.
Speech: I'd love to be able to say to my grandchildren, four years after my first term, I'd like to say, your grandfather, working with the leaders of the Soviet Union, working with the leaders of Europe, was able to ban chemical and biological weapons from the face of the earth.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Lincoln called this country the last best hope of man on earth.
Speech: Lincoln called this country the last best hope of man on earth.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And he was right then, and we still are the last best hope of man on earth.
Speech: And he was right then, and we still are the last best hope of man on earth.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I ask for your support on November 8th.
Speech: And I ask for your support on November 8th.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I will be a good president.
Speech: And I will be a good president.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Working together, we can do wonderful things for the United States and the Free World.
Speech: Working together, we can do wonderful things for the United States and the Free World.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Thank you very, very much.
Speech: Thank you very, very much.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush
